{
  "text": "There may be gender difference in providing emotional support to the elderly. As similar in other countries, daughters in China are usually the main caregivers of older parents. A China-based study did found that having daughters was significantly associated with higher cognitive functions and lower mortality risk than having sons in Chinese elderly [CITATION_1] . If this is the case, those solo-living elderly with only sons who lived far away are most vulnerable to develop adverse mental problems.",
